 "overview": "\u003Cp\u003EA Philanthropic Special Purpose Entity\nWe work to improve educational performance by 1%\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EMission\nThe Maximum Balance Foundation will create a self-sufficient, community empowerment platform from which we will create principled centered leaders of high moral character.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003ECompany Overview\nWhat if there were an innovative, non-profit that would provide self-sustaining revenues and, more importantly, growth sustaining free cash flow and profits? \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EMoreover, what if the non-profit\u0026#8217;s status as a non-profit itself provides the \u0026#8220;killer app\u0026#8221; to exploit a major business paradigm shift? \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EFinally, what if the non-profit\u2019s strategy was to accomplish its goals while changing the face of fundraising from the traditional method of grants and donations, to a model that creates partnerships, where both the partners and benefactors derived significant financial, and civil benefits?\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EHow?\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EFoundations usually try to solve the major social problems of our day - such as poverty, homelessness, global warming, and lack of healthcare - by making grants to nonprofits.\nYet the lack of grant money did not cause these social problems. \u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EInstead, they are often attributable to market failures, where a misalignment between social goals and economic incentives has created or perpetuates social ills.\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003EWe aid in the realignment by engaging activities that foster volunteerism, and mutual respect.\u003C/p\u003E",
